              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A newly-developed, high-efficiency,",
                "light-weight, fast fission chamber, with an improved",
                "discrimination capability between fission and",
                "alpha-decay events, was coupled to 54 EJ-309 liquid",
                "scintillators from the Chi-Nu array to detect",
                "neutrons emitted in fission events."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A high-purity 239Pu target from the JRC-Geel target",
                "preparation laboratory. The fission chamber housed",
                "47 mg of 239Pu arranged in twenty-two deposits and",
                "eleven readout channels, with an alpha-activity of",
                "about 10 MBq per channel, to be compared to a fission",
                "rate of about 15 events/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron beam was produced by spallation and",
                "bombarded 239Pu target after a flight path of about",
                "21.5m. The combined setup and the high recorded",
                "statistics lead to a precise reconstruction of the",
                "PFNS as a function of the incident-neutron energy",
                "Enin, from 0.7 to 700 MeV. The data were obtained",
                "with the double time-of-flight technique and an",
                "innovative setup. It allowed to explicitly account",
                "for experimental systematic bias, which have",
                "hampered the precision and accuracy of existing",
                "experimental results, thus providing more",
                "reliable-than-existing data. Neutron detector",
                "efficiencies were obtained by measuring the PFNS of",
                "the 252Cf spontaneous fission reaction in the same",
                "experimental conditions and with the same analysis",
                "procedure as the 239Pu. For each detector, the",
                "measured 252Cf(sf) PFNS was divided by the evaluated",
                "PFNS standard, normalized to the evaluated ENDF/B-",
                "VIII.0 for 252Cf of (3.759+-0.42%), and used to",
                "evaluate the efficiency of every EJ-309 detector.",
                "Data above 24MeV incident-neutron energy should be",
                "considered as a lower limit as fission neutrons with",
                "energies above 14MeV were not detected."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The absolute statistical and systematic",
                "uncertainties, propagated through the data analysis.",
                "The uncertainty on the 252Cf(sf) nubar, 0.42%, was",
                "not propagated through the data analysis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Data were corrected for four different experimental",
                "biases: the neutron detection energy range, the",
                "presence of a slower incident neutron background",
                " (wrap-around), the limited detector angular",
                "coverage and the detector dead time."
              ]
            }
          ],
